#. type: Title ===
#: administration-linstor.adoc:651
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating and deploying resources/volumes"
msgstr "创建和部署资源/卷"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:654
msgid "In the following scenario we assume that the goal is to create a resource 'backups' with a size of '500 GB' that is replicated among three cluster nodes."
msgstr "在下面的场景中，我们假设目标是创建一个大小为 `500 GB` 的资源 `备份`，该资源在三个集群节点之间复制。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:656
msgid "First, we create a new resource definition:"
msgstr "首先，我们创建一个新的资源定义："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:659
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor resource-definition create backups\n"
msgstr "# linstor resource-definition create backups\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:662
msgid "Second, we create a new volume definition within that resource definition:"
msgstr "其次，我们在该资源定义中创建一个新的卷定义："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:665
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor volume-definition create backups 500G\n"
msgstr "# linstor volume-definition create backups 500G\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:668
msgid "If you want to change the size of the volume-definition you can simply do that by:"
msgstr "如果要更改卷定义的大小，只需执行以下操作："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:671
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor volume-definition set-size backups 0 100G\n"
msgstr "# linstor volume-definition set-size backups 0 100G\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:676
msgid ""
"The parameter `0` is the number of the volume in the resource `backups`. You have to provide this parameter , because resources can have multiple volumes and they are "
"identified by a so called volume-number. This number can be found by listing the volume-definitions."
msgstr "参数 `0` 是资源 `backups` 中的卷数。必须提供此参数，因为资源可以有多个卷，并且它们由所谓的卷号标识。这个数字可以通过列出卷定义来找到。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:679
msgid "The size of a volume-definition can only be decreased if it has no resource. Despite of that the size can be increased even with an deployed resource."
msgstr "只有在没有资源的情况下，才能减小卷定义的大小。尽管如此，即使部署了资源，也可以增加大小。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:683
msgid ""
"So far we have only created objects in LINSTOR's database, not a single LV was created on the storage nodes. Now you have the choice of delegating the task of placement to "
"LINSTOR or doing it yourself."
msgstr "到目前为止，我们只在LINSTOR的数据库中创建了对象，没有在存储节点上创建一个LV。现在你可以选择将安置任务派发给LINSTOR，或者自己做。"

#. type: Title ====
#: administration-linstor.adoc:685
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manual placement"
msgstr "手动放置"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:689
msgid "With the `resource create` command you may assign a resource definition to named nodes explicitly."
msgstr "使用 `resource create` 命令，可以将资源定义显式分配给命名节点。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:694
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor resource create alpha backups --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"
"# linstor resource create bravo backups --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"
"# linstor resource create charlie backups --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor resource create alpha backups --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"
"# linstor resource create bravo backups --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"
"# linstor resource create charlie backups --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"

#. type: Title ====
#: administration-linstor.adoc:697
#, no-wrap
msgid "Autoplace"
msgstr "自动放置"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:701
msgid "The value after autoplace tells LINSTOR how many replicas you want to have.  The storage-pool option should be obvious."
msgstr "autoplace之后的值告诉LINSTOR您想要多少个副本。storage-pool 选项应该很明显。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:703
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor resource create backups --auto-place 3 --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"
msgstr "# linstor resource create backups --auto-place 3 --storage-pool pool_hdd\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:706
msgid "Maybe not so obvious is that you may omit the `--storage-pool` option, then LINSTOR may select a storage pool on its own. The selection follows these rules:"
msgstr "可能不太明显的是，您可以省略 `--storage-pool` 选项，然后LINSTOR可以自己选择一个存储池。选择遵循以下规则："

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:708
msgid "Ignore all nodes and storage pools the current user has no access to"
msgstr "忽略当前用户无权访问的所有节点和存储池"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:709
msgid "Ignore all diskless storage pools"
msgstr "忽略所有无磁盘存储池"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:710
msgid "Ignore all storage pools not having enough free space"
msgstr "忽略没有足够可用空间的所有存储池"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:713
msgid "From the remaining storage pools, LINSTOR currently chooses the one with the most available free space."
msgstr "从剩余的存储池中，LINSTOR会选择可用空间最多的存储池。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:717
msgid ""
"If everything went right the DRBD-resource has now been created by LINSTOR.  This can be checked by looking for the DRBD block device with the `lsblk` command which should look "
"like `drbd0000` or similar."
msgstr "如果一切顺利，DRBD资源现在已经由LINSTOR创建。这时可以通过使用 `lsblk` 命令查找DRBD块设备来检查，设备名应该类似于 `drbd0000` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:721
msgid "Now we should be able to mount the block device of our resource and start using LINSTOR."
msgstr "现在我们应该可以加载我们资源的块设备并开始使用LINSTOR。"

#. type: Title ==
#: administration-linstor.adoc:723
#, no-wrap
msgid "Further LINSTOR tasks"
msgstr "高阶LINSTOR任务"

#. type: Title ===
#: administration-linstor.adoc:726
#, no-wrap
msgid "DRBD clients"
msgstr "DRBD客户端"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:733
msgid ""
"By using the `--drbd-diskless` option instead of `--storage-pool` you can have a permanently diskless DRBD device on a node. This means that the resource will appear as block "
"device and can be mounted to the filesystem without an existing storage-device. The data of the resource is accessed over the network on another nodes with the same resource."
msgstr ""
"通过使用 `--drbd-diskless` 选项而不是 `--storage-pool` ，可以在节点上拥有永久无盘drbd设备。这意味着资源将显示为块设备，并且可以在没有现有存储设备的情况下装载到文件系统。资源的数"
"据通过网络在具有相同资源的其他节点上访问。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:736
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor resource create delta backups --drbd-diskless\n"
msgstr "# linstor resource create delta backups --drbd-diskless\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:740
msgid "The option `--diskless` was deprecated. Please use `--drbd-diskless` or `--nvme-initiator` instead."
msgstr "不推荐使用选项 `--diskless`, 因为已过时。请改用 `--drbd-diskless` 或  `--nvme-initiator` 。"

#. type: Title ===
#: administration-linstor.adoc:742
#, no-wrap
msgid "LINSTOR - DRBD consistency group/multiple volumes"
msgstr "LINSTOR - DRBD一致性组/多个卷"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:747
msgid ""
"The so called consistency group is a feature from DRBD. It is mentioned in this user-guide, due to the fact that one of LINSTOR's main functions is to manage storage-clusters "
"with DRBD. Multiple volumes in one resource are a consistency group."
msgstr "所谓的一致性组是DRBD的一个特性。由于LINSTOR的主要功能之一是使用DRBD管理存储集群，因此本用户指南中提到了这一点。 单个资源中的多个卷是一个一致性组。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:750
msgid "This means that changes on different volumes from one resource are getting replicated in the same chronological order on the other Satellites."
msgstr "这意味着一个资源的不同卷上的更改在其他Satellites上以相同的时间顺序复制。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:753
msgid "Therefore you don't have to worry about the timing if you have interdependent data on different volumes in a resource."
msgstr "因此，如果资源中的不同卷上有相互依赖的数据，也不必担心时间问题。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:755
msgid "To deploy more than one volume in a LINSTOR-resource you have to create two volume-definitions with the same name."
msgstr "要在LINSTOR资源中部署多个卷，必须创建两个同名的卷定义。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:759
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 500G\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 100G\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 500G\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 100G\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: administration-linstor.adoc:763
#, no-wrap
msgid "Volumes of one resource to different Storage-Pools"
msgstr "一个资源到不同存储池的卷"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:766
msgid "This can be achieved by setting the `StorPoolName` property to the volume definitions before the resource is deployed to the nodes:"
msgstr "这可以通过在将资源部署到节点之前将 `StorPoolName` 属性设置为卷定义来实现："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:777
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor resource-definition create backups\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 500G\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 100G\n"
"# linstor volume-definition set-property backups 0 StorPoolName pool_hdd\n"
"# linstor volume-definition set-property backups 1 StorPoolName pool_ssd\n"
"# linstor resource create alpha backups\n"
"# linstor resource create bravo backups\n"
"# linstor resource create charlie backups\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor resource-definition create backups\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 500G\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create backups 100G\n"
"# linstor volume-definition set-property backups 0 StorPoolName pool_hdd\n"
"# linstor volume-definition set-property backups 1 StorPoolName pool_ssd\n"
"# linstor resource create alpha backups\n"
"# linstor resource create bravo backups\n"
"# linstor resource create charlie backups\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:782
msgid ""
"Since the `volume-definition create` command is used without the `--vlmnr` option LINSTOR assigned the volume numbers starting at 0. In the following two lines the 0 and 1 "
"refer to these automatically assigned volume numbers."
msgstr "由于使用 `volume-definition create` 命令时没有使用 `--vlmnr` 选项，因此LINSTOR将从0开始分配卷号。在以下两行中，0和1表示这些自动分配的卷号。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:787
msgid ""
"Here the 'resource create' commands do not need a `--storage-pool` option.  In this case LINSTOR uses a 'fallback' storage pool. Finding that storage pool, LINSTOR queries the "
"properties of the following objects in the following order:"
msgstr "这里的 `resource create` 命令不需要 `--storage-pool` 选项。在这种情况下，LINSTOR使用 `fallback` 存储池。找到该存储池后，LINSTOR按以下顺序查询以下对象的属性："

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:789
msgid "Volume definition"
msgstr "卷定义"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:791
msgid "Resource definition"
msgstr "资源定义"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:795
msgid "If none of those objects contain a `StorPoolName` property, the controller falls back to a hard-coded 'DfltStorPool' string as a storage pool."
msgstr "如果这些对象都不包含 `StorPoolName` 属性，则controller将返回硬编码的 `DfltStorPool` 字符串作为存储池。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:799
msgid ""
"This also means that if you forgot to define a storage pool prior deploying a resource, you will get an error message that LINSTOR could not find the storage pool named "
"'DfltStorPool'."
msgstr "这还意味着，如果在部署资源之前忘记定义存储池，则会收到一条错误消息，即LINSTOR找不到名为 `DfltStorPool` 的存储池。"

#. type: Title ===
#: administration-linstor.adoc:802
#, no-wrap
msgid "LINSTOR without DRBD"
msgstr "无DRBD的LINSTOR"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:807
msgid ""
"LINSTOR can be used without DRBD as well. Without DRBD, LINSTOR is able to provision volumes from LVM and ZFS backed storage pools, and create those volumes on individual nodes "
"in your LINSTOR cluster."
msgstr "LINSTOR也可以在没有DRBD的情况下使用。没有DRBD，LINSTOR能够从LVM和ZFS支持的存储池中配置卷，并在LINSTOR集群中的各个节点上创建这些卷。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:811
msgid ""
"Currently LINSTOR supports the creation of LVM and ZFS volumes with the option of layering some combinations of LUKS, DRBD, and/or NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP on top of those volumes."
msgstr "目前，LINSTOR支持创建LVM和ZFS卷，可以选择在这些卷上分层luk、DRBD和/或/NVMe-TCP的NVMe的某些组合。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:814
msgid "For example, assume we have a Thin LVM backed storage pool defined in our LINSTOR cluster named, `thin-lvm`:"
msgstr "例如，我们在LINSTOR集群中定义了一个Thin LVM支持的存储池，名为 `thin-lvm`:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:825
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor --no-utf8 storage-pool list\n"
"+--------------------------------------------------------------+\n"
"| StoragePool | Node      | Driver   | PoolName          | ... |\n"
"|--------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-a | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-b | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-c | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-d | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"+--------------------------------------------------------------+\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor --no-utf8 storage-pool list\n"
"+--------------------------------------------------------------+\n"
"| StoragePool | Node      | Driver   | PoolName          | ... |\n"
"|--------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-a | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-b | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-c | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"| thin-lvm    | linstor-d | LVM_THIN | drbdpool/thinpool | ... |\n"
"+--------------------------------------------------------------+\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:829
msgid "We could use LINSTOR to create a Thin LVM on `linstor-d` that's 100GiB in size using the following commands:"
msgstr "我们可以使用LINSTOR在 `linstor-d` 上创建一个100GiB大小的精简LVM，使用以下命令："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:835
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor resource-definition create rsc-1\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create rsc-1 100GiB\n"
"# linstor resource create --layer-list storage \\\n"
"          --storage-pool thin-lvm linstor-d rsc-1\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor resource-definition create rsc-1\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create rsc-1 100GiB\n"
"# linstor resource create --layer-list storage \\\n"
"          --storage-pool thin-lvm linstor-d rsc-1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:840
msgid ""
"You should then see you have a new Thin LVM on `linstor-d`. You can extract the device path from LINSTOR by listing your linstor resources with the `--machine-readable` flag "
"set:"
msgstr "你应该看到 `linstor-d` 上有一个新的瘦LVM。通过使用 `--machine-readable` 标志集列出LINSTOR资源，可以从LINSTOR提取设备路径："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:844
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor --machine-readable resource list | grep device_path\n"
"            \"device_path\": \"/dev/drbdpool/rsc-1_00000\",\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor --machine-readable resource list | grep device_path\n"
"            \"device_path\": \"/dev/drbdpool/rsc-1_00000\",\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:849
msgid ""
"If you wanted to layer DRBD on top of this volume, which is the default `--layer-list` option in LINSTOR for ZFS or LVM backed volumes, you would use the following resource "
"creation pattern instead:"
msgstr "如果要将DRBD放置在此卷上（这是LINSTOR中ZFS或LVM支持的卷的默认 `--layer-list` 选项），可以使用以下资源创建模式："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:855
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor resource-definition create rsc-1\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create rsc-1 100GiB\n"
"# linstor resource create --layer-list drbd,storage \\\n"
"          --storage-pool thin-lvm linstor-d rsc-1\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor resource-definition create rsc-1\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create rsc-1 100GiB\n"
"# linstor resource create --layer-list drbd,storage \\\n"
"          --storage-pool thin-lvm linstor-d rsc-1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:859
msgid "You would then see that you have a new Thin LVM backing a DRBD volume on `linstor-d`:"
msgstr "然后，您将看到有一个新的 Thin LVM被创建出来用于支撑 `linstor-d` 上的DRBD卷："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:864
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor --machine-readable resource list | grep -e device_path -e backing_disk\n"
"            \"device_path\": \"/dev/drbd1000\",\n"
"            \"backing_disk\": \"/dev/drbdpool/rsc-1_00000\",\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor --machine-readable resource list | grep -e device_path -e backing_disk\n"
"            \"device_path\": \"/dev/drbd1000\",\n"
"            \"backing_disk\": \"/dev/drbdpool/rsc-1_00000\",\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:867
msgid "The following table shows which layer can be followed by which child-layer:"
msgstr "下表显示了哪个层可以后跟哪个子层："

#. type: Table
#: administration-linstor.adoc:877
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Layer | Child layer\n"
"\n"
"| DRBD | WRITECACHE, NVME, LUKS, STORAGE\n"
"| WRITECACHE | NVME, LUKS, STORAGE\n"
"| NVME | WRITACACHE, LUKS, STORAGE\n"
"| LUKS | STORAGE\n"
"| STORAGE | -\n"
msgstr ""
"| Layer | Child layer\n"
"\n"
"| DRBD | WRITECACHE, NVME, LUKS, STORAGE\n"
"| WRITECACHE | NVME, LUKS, STORAGE\n"
"| NVME | WRITACACHE, LUKS, STORAGE\n"
"| LUKS | STORAGE\n"
"| STORAGE | -\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:880
msgid "One layer can only occur once in the layer-list"
msgstr "一个层只能在层列表中出现一次"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:883
msgid "For information about the prerequisites for the `luks` layer, refer to the Encrypted Volumes section of this User's Guide."
msgstr "有关 `luks`层的先决条件的信息，请参阅本用户指南的加密卷部分。"

#. type: Title ====
#: administration-linstor.adoc:884
#, no-wrap
msgid "NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP LINSTOR Layer"
msgstr "NVME-OF/NVME-TCP Linstor Layer"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:893
msgid ""
"NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP allows LINSTOR to connect diskless resources to a node with the same resource where the data is stored over NVMe fabrics. This leads to the advantage that "
"resources can be mounted without using local storage by accessing the data over the network.  LINSTOR is not using DRBD in this case, and therefore NVMe resources provisioned "
"by LINSTOR are not replicated, the data is stored on one node."
msgstr ""
"NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP允许LINSTOR将无盘资源连接到具有相同资源的节点，数据存储在NVMe结构上。这就带来了这样一个优势：通过网络访问数据，无需使用本地存储就可以装载资源。在这种情况下，"
"LINSTOR不使用DRBD，因此不会复制LINSTOR提供的NVMe资源，数据存储在一个节点上。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:899
msgid ""
"NVMe-oF only works on RDMA-capable networks and NVMe-TCP on every network that can carry IP traffic. If you want to know more about NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP visit https://www.linbit."
"com/en/nvme-linstor-swordfish/ for more information."
msgstr ""
"NVMe-oF仅在支持RDMA的网络上工作，NVMe-TCP在每个可以承载IP流量的网络上工作。如果您想了解有关NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP的NVMe的更多信息，请访问https://www.linbit.com/en/nvme-linstor-"
"swordfish/。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:903
msgid "To use NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP with LINSTOR the package `nvme-cli` needs to be installed on every Node which acts as a Satellite and will use NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP for a resource:"
msgstr "要将NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP与LINSTOR一起使用，需要在充当Satellite的每个节点上安装包 `nvme-cli`，并将NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP用于资源："

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:906
msgid "If you are not using Ubuntu use the suitable command for installing packages on your OS - SLES: zypper - CentOS: yum"
msgstr "如果不使用Ubuntu，请使用合适的命令在OS安装软件包 - SLES: zypper - CentOS: yum"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:909
#, no-wrap
msgid "# apt install nvme-cli\n"
msgstr "# apt install nvme-cli\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:913
msgid "To make a resource which uses NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP an additional parameter has to be given as you create the resource-definition:"
msgstr "要使资源使用NVMe-oF/NVMe-TCP，必须在创建资源定义时提供一个附加参数："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:916
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor resource-definition create nvmedata  -l nvme,storage\n"
msgstr "# linstor resource-definition create nvmedata  -l nvme,storage\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:922
msgid ""
"As default the -l (layer-stack) parameter is set to `drbd, storage` when DRBD is used. If you want to create LINSTOR resources with neither NVMe nor DRBD you have to set the `-"
"l` parameter to only `storage`."
msgstr "默认情况下，使用DRBD时-l（layer-stack）参数设置为 `drbd, storage`。如果要创建既不使用NVMe也不使用DRBD的LINSTOR资源，则必须将 `-l` 参数设置为仅使用 `storage`。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:924
msgid "Create the volume-definition for our resource:"
msgstr "为我们的资源创建卷定义："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:927
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor volume-definition create nvmedata 500G\n"
msgstr "# linstor volume-definition create nvmedata 500G\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:932
msgid "Before you create the resource on your nodes you have to know where the data will be stored locally and which node accesses it over the network."
msgstr "在节点上创建资源之前，必须知道数据将在本地存储在哪里，以及哪个节点通过网络访问它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:934
msgid "First we create the resource on the node where our data will be stored:"
msgstr "首先，我们在存储数据的节点上创建资源："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:937
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor resource create alpha nvmedata --storage-pool pool_ssd\n"
msgstr "# linstor resource create alpha nvmedata --storage-pool pool_ssd\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:941
msgid "On the nodes where the resource-data will be accessed over the network, the resource has to be defined as diskless:"
msgstr "在将通过网络访问资源数据的节点上，必须将资源定义为无盘："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:944
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor resource create beta nvmedata -d\n"
msgstr "# linstor resource create beta nvmedata -d\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:947
msgid "The `-d` parameter creates the resource on this node as diskless."
msgstr "`-d` 参数将此节点上的资源创建为无盘。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:950
msgid "Now you can mount the resource `nvmedata` on one of your nodes."
msgstr "现在，您可以在一个节点上装载资源 `nvmedata`。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:954
msgid "If your nodes have more than one NIC you should force the route between them for NVMe-of/NVME-TCP, otherwise multiple NIC's could cause troubles."
msgstr "如果您的节点有多个NIC，您应该为NVMe-of/NVME-TCP指定它们之间的路由，否则多个NIC可能会导致问题。"

#. type: Title ====
#: administration-linstor.adoc:956
#, no-wrap
msgid "Writecache Layer"
msgstr "写入缓存层"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:962
msgid ""
"A https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/admin-guide/device-mapper/writecache.html[DM-Writecache] device is composed by two devices, one storage device and one cache device.  "
"LINSTOR can setup such a writecache device, but needs some additional information, like the storage pool and the size of the cache device."
msgstr ""
"一个 https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/admin-guide/device-mapper/writecache.html[DM writecache] 设备由两个设备、即一个存储设备和一个缓存设备组成。LINSTOR可以设置这样一个"
"writecache设备，但是需要一些额外的信息，比如存储池和缓存设备的大小。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:966
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor storage-pool create lvm node1 lvmpool drbdpool\n"
"# linstor storage-pool create lvm node1 pmempool pmempool\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor storage-pool create lvm node1 lvmpool drbdpool\n"
"# linstor storage-pool create lvm node1 pmempool pmempool\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:969
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor resource-definition create r1\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create r1 100G\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor resource-definition create r1\n"
"# linstor volume-definition create r1 100G\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:972
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor volume-definition set-property r1 0 Writecache/PoolName pmempool\n"
"# linstor volume-definition set-property r1 0 Writecache/Size 1%\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor volume-definition set-property r1 0 Writecache/PoolName pmempool\n"
"# linstor volume-definition set-property r1 0 Writecache/Size 1%\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:974
#, no-wrap
msgid "# linstor resource create node1 r1 --storage-pool lvmpool --layer-list WRITECACHE,STORAGE\n"
msgstr "# linstor resource create node1 r1 --storage-pool lvmpool --layer-list WRITECACHE,STORAGE\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:981
msgid ""
"The two properties set in the examples are mandatory, but can also be set on controller level which would act as a default for all resources with `WRITECACHE` in their `--layer-"
"list`. However, please note that the `Writecache/PoolName` referes to the corresponding node. If the node does not have a storge-pool named `pmempool` you will get an error "
"message."
msgstr ""
"示例中设置的两个属性是必需的，但也可以在controller级别上设置，这将作为其 `层列表` 中包含 `WRITECACHE` 的所有资源的默认值。但是，请注意， `Writecache/PoolName` 指的是相应的节点。"
"如果节点没有名为 `pmempool` 的存储池，则会收到错误消息。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:988
msgid ""
"The 4 mandatory parameters required by https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/admin-guide/device-mapper/writecache.html[DM-Writecache] are either configured via property or "
"figured out by LINSTOR.  The optional properties listed in the mentioned link can also be set via property.  Please see `linstor controller set-property --help` for a list of "
"`Writecache/*` property-keys."
msgstr ""
"在 https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/admin-guide/device-mapper/writecache.html[DM writecache] 中所需的4个必需参数要么通过属性配置，要么由LINSTOR计算。上述链接中列出的可选属"
"性也可以通过属性进行设置。有关 `Writecache/*` 属性键的列表，请参见 `linstor controller set property--help` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:992
msgid ""
"Using `--layer-list DRBD,WRITECACHE,STORAGE` while having DRBD configured to use external metadata, only the backing device will use a writecache, not the device holding the "
"external metadata."
msgstr "使用 `--layer-list DRBD,WRITECACHE,STORAGE` 将DRBD配置为使用外部元数据时，只有备份设备将使用writecache，而不是保存外部元数据的设备。"

#. type: Title ===
#: administration-linstor.adoc:994
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing Network Interface Cards"
msgstr "管理网络接口卡"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:998
msgid "LINSTOR can deal with multiple network interface cards (NICs) in a machine, they are called `netif` in LINSTOR speak."
msgstr "LINSTOR可以在一台机器上处理多个网络接口卡（NICs），在LINSTOR中称为 `netif`。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:1002
msgid ""
"When a satellite node is created a first `netif` gets created implicitly with the name `default`. Using the `--interface-name` option of the `node create` command you can give "
"it a different name."
msgstr "创建附属节点时，将隐式创建第一个名为 `default` 的 `netif` 。使用 `node create` 命令的 `--interface name` 选项，可以给它一个不同的名称。"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:1004
msgid "Additional NICs are created like this:"
msgstr "其他NIC的创建方式如下："

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:1007
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor node interface create alpha 100G_nic 192.168.43.221\n"
"# linstor node interface create alpha 10G_nic 192.168.43.231\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor node interface create alpha 100G_nic 192.168.43.221\n"
"# linstor node interface create alpha 10G_nic 192.168.43.231\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:1013
msgid ""
"NICs are identified by the IP address only, the name is arbitrary and is *not* related to the interface name used by Linux. The NICs can be assigned to storage pools so that "
"whenever a resource is created in such a storage pool, the DRBD traffic will be routed through the specified NIC."
msgstr "NIC仅由IP地址标识，名称是任意的，与Linux使用的接口名称 *无关* 。可以将NIC分配给存储池，以便每当在这样的存储池中创建资源时，DRBD通信通过其指定的NIC路由。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: administration-linstor.adoc:1017
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# linstor storage-pool set-property alpha pool_hdd PrefNic 10G_nic\n"
"# linstor storage-pool set-property alpha pool_ssd PrefNic 100G_nic\n"
msgstr ""
"# linstor storage-pool set-property alpha pool_hdd PrefNic 10G_nic\n"
"# linstor storage-pool set-property alpha pool_ssd PrefNic 100G_nic\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: administration-linstor.adoc:1021
msgid "FIXME describe how to route the controller +<->+ client communication through a specific `netif`."
msgstr "FIXME 描述了如何通过特定的 `netif` 路由controller +<->+ 客户端通信。"

#. type: Title ===
